Vincent J. CANNARA, Appellant, v. STATE OF NEW JERSEY and Paul Kiernan Sr., Sheriff of Monmouth County. No. 19400. United States Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Jan. 25, 1972. Decided March 9, 1972. Avrom J. Gold, Mandelbaum, Mandel-baum & Gold, Newark, N.J., for appellant. Frederick J. Kalma, Asst. Prosecutor, Freehold, N.J., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS and VAN DUSEN, Circuit Judges.

OPINION OF THE COURT

PER CURIAM:

We have examined the record in this case and can perceive no error. The contentions of the relator-appellant are without merit. The judgment will be affirmed.
